      "content": "---\n\nOur new database engine, DataStream, employs advanced techniques to ensure data persistence and concurrency. At its core, DataStream utilizes a Log-Structured Merge-Tree (LSM-Tree) to efficiently handle write operations, leveraging Write-Ahead Logging (WAL) to maintain data integrity. The engine supports ACID compliance, ensuring atomicity, consistency, isolation, and durability of transactions.\n\nDataStream's concurrency control is achieved through a combination of techniques, including Two-Phase Commit (2PC), Quorum-based replication, and Consensus algorithms to ensure data consistency across distributed systems. We employ a sophisticated Query Optimizer that uses indexes, hash joins, and nested loop joins to minimize latency and maximize throughput.\n\nTo handle high-throughput workloads, DataStream implements a Buffer Pool to reduce I/O operations and employs techniques like Read-Ahead and Write-Amplification to enhance performance. The engine also supports advanced features like Sharding and Replication to distribute data across multiple nodes, ensuring high availability and fault tolerance.\n\nDataStream's architecture is designed to handle complex queries efficiently, utilizing techniques like Full Table Scans, Foreign Key constraints, and Unique Constraints to maintain data integrity. The engine also supports advanced features like Triggers, Stored Procedures, and Views to",
